  "text": "This test basically works by loading a known force (in grams) via a diamond indenter to the top or bottom surface of the sample for a specific time (in seconds). The commonest indenters used in the literature are the Knoop (KHN) and the Vickers (VH) indenters, both of which are easy to use. Studies have reported a high correlation between microhardness and DC [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
